  "securityBoundaries": [
    "No deployment manifest is usable until all 12 addresses, runtime hashes, verification URLs, audit evidence, and release approval are populated.",
    "Runtime verification is an SDK-issued capability; caller-built or cloned proof objects are rejected.",
    "Prepared actions are builder-issued capabilities, must pass an exact fresh simulation, and cannot be relabeled before wallet submission.",
    "The SDK never accepts a private key, silently selects an RPC, or switches a user's chain.",
    "Phase-0 smart-account submission requires SDK-sealed account, factory, entry-point, validation, recovery, and passkey runtime verification plus exact fresh simulation and provider-result binding; live installed-policy and revocation conformance remains external.",
    "Smart-account creation, passkey enrollment, signer rotation, and recovery are one-time-approval, expiry, revision, commitment, transition, and readback bound; selecting and qualifying a production provider remains external.",
    "Paymaster adapters are quote-only; provider payloads cannot submit or prove sponsorship, and every quote is bound to exact action, canonical policy commitment, gas, rate, and expiry policy.",
    "Blocked-attempt calldata is adapter-only and never becomes a wallet PreparedRobinhoodAction; the registry persists a failure reason without consuming a grant or executing a target.",
    "Indexer and offline-cache state is public and read-only; page sizes, pagination, and retries are bounded, snapshot changes fail, and reorged descendants invalidate.",
    "Economic finality requires sealed transaction-intent readback plus two independent L2 readers and two independent L1 batch readers.",
    "The Virtuals validator is an offline structural check; it cannot prove platform acceptance, legal eligibility, ownership, code deployment, or launch finality."
